&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nubank is looking for a senior Corporate Development professional to be our permanent presence in San Francisco — the heart of global innovation in crypto, AI, and fintech. Sitting within the Global Corporate Development team, this person will be our eyes and ears in the US startup ecosystem, identifying and leading strategic opportunities that support Nubank’s international growth agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The initial focus is crypto: sourcing and executing acquihires and acquisitions, building relationships with founders, operators, and investors across the Bay Area ecosystem. Over time, the mandate will evolve — spanning AI partnerships, design talent pipelines, and opportunistic fintech M&amp;amp;A — as Nubank’s Bay Area footprint grows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-autonomy role for someone who thrives in a fast-moving, entrepreneurial environment and can operate independently while staying tightly connected to a globally distributed team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be Nubank’s presence in the Bay Area.&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the primary point of contact with the US startup ecosystem — founders, VCs, investment banks, and strategic partners — with a focus on crypto and AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead crypto M&amp;amp;A.&lt;/strong&gt; Source, evaluate, and execute acquihires and acquisitions in the crypto/Web3 space. Own deal flow from initial contact through term sheet and close, in coordination with the LatAm CorpDev team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build and maintain a high-quality network.&lt;/strong&gt; Develop trusted relationships with crypto and AI founders, VC and crypto-native funds, accelerators, and ecosystem intermediaries in the Bay Area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify and lead strategic opportunities.&lt;/strong&gt; Beyond crypto, keep a watching brief on AI, design, and other fields relevant to Nubank’s global strategy. Surface and prioritize the right opportunities in partnership with team leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive cross-functional execution.&lt;/strong&gt; Lead end-to-end execution of prioritized transactions and partnerships, coordinating workstreams across CorpDev, Legal, Finance, and business units.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Write high-quality investment and partnership memos.&lt;/strong&gt; Synthesize complex opportunities into clear, hypothesis-driven briefs for Nubank’s senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support Nu USA CorpDev activities.&lt;/strong&gt; On a secondary basis, provide deal and market intelligence relevant to Nu’s US business (this is not the primary mandate of the role).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
